Program: Free Thinking
Title: Paolozzi, Daniel Dennett
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b08dnrxw
Last Broadcast Date: Wed 15 Feb 2017
Dubbed the "godfather of British pop art", Eduardo Paolozzi (1924-2005) is the subject of an exhibition at London's Whitechapel Gallery. Philip Dodd and his guests art historians Richard Cork and Judith Collins, philosopher Barry Smith and writer Iain Sinclair discuss Paolozzi's legacy. Plus an interview with American philosopher Professor Daniel Dennett Co-Director Center for Cognitive Studies at Tufts University. Eduardo Paolozzi runs at the Whitechapel Gallery in London from 16 February - 14 May 2017 Daniel Dennett's latest book is called From Bacteria to Bach and Back. Producer Torquil MacLeod. Show less